  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <note><para>If you need a plugin for a given dependency, that dependency
      needs to be installed before this application.
    </para></note>

    <para>
      If you have installed <xref linkend="openjpeg2"/> and wish to use it with
      GStreamer Bad Plug-ins, apply the following patch:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -p1 -i ../gst-plugins-bad-&gst-plugins-bad-version;-openjpeg21-1.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Suppress installation of unnecessary files:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed "s/ install-data-local//" -i docs/libs/Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-data-local//" -i docs/plugins/Makefile.in</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Prepare the package for compilation:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix= \
            --disable-nls
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>porg -lD "make -j1 install &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstbadbase-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstbadvideo-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstbasecamerabinsrc-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstcodecparsers-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstinsertbin-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstmpegts-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgstphotography-1.0.la &amp;&amp;
rm -v /lib/libgsturidownloader-1.0.la"</userinput></screen>

